<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-17T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                                Indonesia/12–1848: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                                    </gloss>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-18T11:00:00+08:00">December 18, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received December 18—10:02 a. m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1107. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 492.1 delivered to
                                Schuurman December 18, 9:40 a. m., following letter dated Kaliurang
                                December 17 addressed Schuurman signed Cochran.</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text printed in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd yr., Suppl.</hi> (Dec.), page 220.]</p>
                            <p>Signed Cochran.<note n="1" xml:id="d429fn1">For reply by the acting
                                    chairman of the Netherlands delegation, dated Batavia, December
                                    20, see <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd
                                        yr., Suppl.</hi> (Dec.), p. 241. The text was transmitted in
                                    telegram 1127, December 21, noon, from Batavia (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 502), and repeated in
                                    telegram 4901, December 22, 7 p. m., to Paris (for
                                    Jessup).</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>